WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:06.601
This Core edition shows how to build a new client’s file from source evidence.

2
00:00:06.601 --> 00:00:07.940
The model connects

3
00:00:10.968 --> 00:00:14.538
five elements: incoming documents and where they came from;

4
00:00:14.538 --> 00:00:18.108
client identity and the people involved; requested services

5
00:00:21.136 --> 00:00:25.046
and engagement facts; open requests with their next actions;

6
00:00:25.046 --> 00:00:28.696
and dates and history maintained over time. The elements

7
00:00:31.724 --> 00:00:33.955
remain distinct but connected,

8
00:00:33.955 --> 00:00:38.864
so every fact can be traced to the document or decision behind it.

9
00:00:41.892 --> 00:00:47.916
Each country maps its own documents, checks and rules onto this shared structure.

10
00:00:47.916 --> 00:00:49.032
The result is a

11
00:00:52.060 --> 00:00:55.019
readable client file that shows what is known,

12
00:00:55.019 --> 00:00:59.200
what remains open and how the professional relationship develops.
